---
description: Economics research safety and reproducibility standards for the Padova Card-Krueger workshop repository.
globs: "**/*.md, **/*.py, **/*.tex, **/*.bib, examples/card-krueger/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Read `AGENTS.md`, the relevant README, and any data source map before editing.
- Keep changes scoped to the active issue or prompt.
- Do not inspect, print, or edit `.env`, `secrets/`, `data/raw/`, or
  `data/private/` without explicit human approval.
- Do not modify `examples/card-krueger/data/synthetic_fast_food_panel.csv` unless
  the issue explicitly allows a teaching fixture update.
- Preserve the synthetic-data caveat for any Card-Krueger result, figure, memo,
  or slide.
- Do not invent citations, coefficients, standard errors, sample sizes, or
  robustness results.
- Report exact verification commands and outcomes before claiming completion.
- Route nontrivial empirical changes through `research-sdd`, then ask a read-only
  reviewer subagent to check the result.
